$BHC I'm pretty much done with the first $100k I invested. Don't care if it goes to $0 - still young and I'm working on the second pot to invest in the next 2-3 years. At the end of the day you invest because you have a value thesis, and that thesis hasn't changed with BHC. If you can't live up to that thesis, then you're better off on the casino floor than equities. You might as well throw out all the finance books, delete all the DCF and relative valuation models, and just roll a dice for any financial decision. I don't expect this value to be realized anytime soon, but it will happen, either through an eventual higher EBITDA multiple, B/O, or a general return to favor for the sector. I know this post wreaks of all types of behavioral biases, but there's a thin line between conviction and a bias. I've been long since 2016, got in and out at various levels and finally settled with a price of $21. It's been a hell of a ride, and its an exciting time to be a part of this stock.
